cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to predict human activities from user-generated content. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related areas. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) another likely sub-category. The use of a neural network model for prediction makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of user traits, which makes cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible sub-category.
